# Login Page Description and Functional Specifications
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The login page provides access to the application. Users are required to enter a valid username and password combination in order to access the system. 

** THE LOGIN PAGE **
The login-page will consist of the following attributes:
- Username: textbox not accept inputs longer than 15 characters. (See USERNAME REQUIREMENRS section for full details)
- Password: textbox that accepts letters, numbers and special characters AND not accept inputs longer than 8 characters. (See PASSWORD REQUIREMENRS section for full details)
- Forgot_Password link: when this link is clicked the user will be redirected to a forgot-password page which will be described in the FORGOT PASSWORD PAGE section below.
- Login button: this button should by default be disabled and will only be enabled when a username is entered AND password field contains at least 4 characters, No validation done here.

** USERNAME REQUIREMENTS **
Username may contain:
- Letters (A–Z, a–z).
- Underscores (_).
- Must not contain spaces or other special characters.
- May not be greater than 15 characters.
- May not contain spaces.

** PASSWORD REQUIREMENTS **
For a password to be considered valid it should contain the following:
- Minimum of 4 characters.
- Contain at least 1 uppercase letter.
- Contain at least 1 number.
- Should not be greater than 8 characters.
- May not contain spaces.

** FORGOT PASSWORD PAGE **
When the user clicks the forgot password link on the login-page, the user should be redirected to the forgot-password page. This page will function as follows:
- The forgot-password page will prompt the user to enter a username.
- Then user will click the submit button.
- if the username is valid, an email with a link will be sent to the users email address AND a message displayed to the user which reads "Password reset email sent, Please check your inbox and click the reset link".
- when the user opens the email sent and clicks the link, the user should be redirected on a reset-password page and prompted to enter and confirm the new password. (See RESET PASSWORD PAGE section for full details)
- if the username is NOT found, the user should remain on the forgot-password page and a message is displayed "username not found".

** RESET PASSWORD PAGE **
On this page, the user will be prompted to enter the following:
- New Password: should conform to the PASSWORD REQUIREMENTS.
- Confirm Password: should match the New Password field.
- Reset button: when clicked and the new password and confirm password has matched and passed checks updates the users password. A Message is displayed in the center of the screen in green which reads "Password
                has been updated successfully. You will be redirected to the login page in 5 seconds".
- After 5 seconds the user should automatically be redirected to the login-page.
- Reset link is valid for 5 minutes and can only be used once.

** LOGIN **
The Login button when clicked should redirect the user to the dashboard page if the username AND password is valid. If the username OR password is invalid, a message should be displayed 
"Incorrect login username or password, please try again".

** MESSAGES & ERROR HANDLING **
All error messages will be displayed as follows:
- The field containing the error will be highlighted in red.
- The error messages will be displayed below the field in red.
All other messages will be displayed as follows:
- Messages will be displayed in the top center of the screen, unless otherwise indicated.
- Messages indicating successful interactions will be displayed in green.

